ibution, irrespective of the shape and amplitude of the linear power\nspectrum. They are also consistent with the observed line-width distribution\ngiven the large uncertainties. Our joint analysis suggests that \\sigma_8 is\nlikely to be in the range 0.7 - 0.9 for a temperature 10000K<T<20000K and a\nreasonable reionization history.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 26 Oct 2004 08:37:22 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 9 Jun 2005 10:29:38 GMT"}],"update_date":"2009-11-10"}
